&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Story:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Story Cannabis was built by misfits on a mission — people bold enough to shift the cannabis narrative and create something better. Founded in 2021 by industry veterans, Story is a vertically integrated company headquartered in Phoenix, operating across Arizona, Maryland, Ohio, and Louisiana, and we’re just getting started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to bring hope, happiness, and healing to the world through cannabis, and we’re doing it one state, one store, and one customer at a time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leadership defines how we show up. Data drives how we grow. Gratitude keeps us grounded. Unity fuels our momentum. And growth, in every sense, inspires everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to challenge what’s expected and shape the future of cannabis, your next chapter starts with Story.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Story is adopting a Default-to-AI strategy—if AI can reliably automate or materially improve a process, we deploy it. As the Accounting &amp;amp; Finance AI Automation Manager, you will design and implement AI-driven systems that transform Accounting, Finance, and adjacent functions into a real-time, scalable operating platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working directly with our Finance and Accounting leadership team to align on clearly defined priorities, you will deliver measurable impact through automation, improved data integrity, and faster decision-making. This role offers a unique opportunity to help architect the future of Story’s AI-enabled operating model across multiple platforms and workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and deploy AI-enabled workflows across Accounting, Finance, and operational functions to materially reduce manual effort, improve accuracy, and accelerate time-to-close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate reconciliations, journal entries, accrual calculations, and close processes to create a more efficient and scalable monthly and quarterly close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate AI across financial and operational systems (ERP, POS, inventory, FP&amp;amp;A tools, data warehouses) to improve data integrity, consistency, and real-time visibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design intelligent workflows that transform finance from a periodic reporting function into a continuous, real-time operating platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and maintain existing AI and automation workflows ensuring ongoing reliability, performance, and audit readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve automated processes supporting AP accruals, prepaids, fixed assets, lease accounting, intercompany, and other complex accounting areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor AI workflow performance and proactively identify opportunities to improve accuracy, speed, and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish standardized automation frameworks that can be deployed consistently across multiple business units and entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead AI initiatives from concept through pilot, testing, deployment, and enterprise-scale rollout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define project roadmaps, milestones, and measurable ROI targets tied to efficiency gains, cost reduction, and improved financial insight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement repeatable automation patterns that can scale across multiple workflows and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive a culture of continuous improvement aligned with a Default-to-AI operating philosophy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
