&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Monday-Friday from 6:30 AM- 3:00 PM (&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MUST&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;complete delivery route prior to leaving for the day/ potential overtime&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Distribution Associate/Driver will work to deliver items to clients or businesses in a safe, timely manner. This person will be responsible for reviewing orders before and after delivery to ensure that orders are complete, the charges are correct, and the customer is satisfied.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load the delivery van at the beginning of the day for deliveries that will happen throughout the day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret and execute state laws and regulations required when delivering medical cannabis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of vehicle maintenance and ability to complete routine maintenance tasks (changing tires, check and add fluids, etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage documents associated with medical cannabis delivery, ensuring that proper documents are kept and manifests are returned completed and ready for filing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining positive professional relationships with dispensary staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Timely and effective communication when issues arise while making deliveries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains accurate daily records of orders fulfilled and deliveries made.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs all duties related to order fulfillment and delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducts audits of all incoming and outgoing inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma or G.E.D required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience with inventory preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a clean motor vehicle driving record (minor violations may be considered).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a valid drivers license.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be at least 21 years of age and able to obtain/maintain all state-required cannabis badging, which includes a pre-employment background check.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Requirements &amp;amp; Work Environment:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be capable of sitting, squatting, standing, kneeling, bending, or walking for long durations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have the ability to push, pull, or lift a minimum of 50 pounds.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allergen warnings - Potential exposure to dust, pollen, and plant pathogens.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
