&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Regional Retail Director partners closely with the Vice President of Retail and cross-functional leaders to ensure best-in-class store operations, compliance, customer experience, and team development. Retail District Managers within the assigned markets will look to this role for operational oversight and alignment while maintaining their direct reporting relationship to the VP of Retail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and develop a team of Regional and Retail Operations leaders and District Managers, building strong bench strength and succession plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistent leadership expectations, performance management, and professional development across all retail management levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of accountability, collaboration, and continuous improvement aligned with Story’s values and support VP of Retail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serves as the primary owner of national retail operational governance, including SOP, compliance execution standards, audit readiness, and system adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures operational issues are resolved through regional /district leadership rather than direct store-level intervention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Marketing, Merchandising, HR, Compliance, IT, Finance, and Supply Chain to ensure retail needs are supported and brand standards are upheld.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key liaison between corporate strategy and field execution, ensuring alignment, clarity, and follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with retail leadership to support sales growth, labor optimization, and margin improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support budgeting, forecasting, and labor management efforts by ensuring operational alignment to financial targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze sales data, market performance, and customer insights to inform operational improvements and strategic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and evolve the national retail operating model, ensuring consistent execution of standards, SOPs, and best practices across all markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, implement, and continuously improve standard operating procedures (SOPs), internal processes, and compliance training for all retail locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review daily, weekly, and monthly performance metrics across all stores, identifying trends, risks, and opportunities; drive corrective action plans where performance gaps exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee inventory, point-of-sale, and compliance systems to ensure accuracy, adoption, and audit readiness across all markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute standardized audit programs to enforce compliance, operational discipline, and reporting accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a liaison between corporate strategy and field execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
