&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Assistant General Manager reports directly to the General Manager and is responsible for developing a high-performing team that consistently delivers top-line sales growth. This person will lead and support the staff with customer service, sales training, product knowledge, leadership development, inventory controls, and compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with the General Manager to plan and implement sales strategies to drive positive sales growth within the dispensary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining strong inventory controls and making sure that the store is upholding compliance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coaching, training, and developing staff, making sure they are aligned with the company&#39;s goals and vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with the General Manager to help create, monitor, and track the store&#39;s KPIs, and leveraging data to help drive decisions around labor costs, sales strategies, and training opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping to hire, train and onboard new staff within the dispensary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with the store&#39;s day-to-day operations and partnering with other internal teams, such as marketing, retail operations, and supply chain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum High School Diploma or G.E.D equivalent required, Associate Degree preferred.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of management experience in a high-volume retail environment with previous cannabis experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with point of sales systems and backend compliance tools, such as Dutchie and Metrc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership qualities and the ability to recruit and train staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and customer service skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical with the ability to set and track store KPIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open availability with no scheduling conflicts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to occasionally lift 50+ pounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to either sit or stand for long periods of time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time off (PTO) including 8 paid holidays per year*&lt;/li&gt;
