&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Inventory Lead supports the Inventory Manager in the daily operations of inventory control, focusing on executing inventory-related tasks, supervising Inventory Associates, and maintaining a highly organized back-of-house and front-of-house supply of inventory. The Lead ensures procedures are followed and that the product is stored and handled correctly, maintaining quality and compliance. The Lead also plays a crucial role in the oversight of inventory turnover and assists retail management in optimizing inventory processes to ensure efficiency and accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and manage inventory levels using inventory management software such as Dutchie, Lucid ID, and where applicable, Metrc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the processing and storage of incoming inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tag and label inventory and update system records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with daily inventory counts and reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train staff on proper inventory handling and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Inventory Manager with data entry and record-keeping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise Inventory Associates and delegate tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise that all inventory restock is done before the end of shift by the Inventory Associate or Inventory Manager on duty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all End of Batch Metrc Tags are completed prior to end of shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with conducting weekly audits and reporting any variances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all variances are investigated to their full ability. Holding employees accountable when mistakes are made.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and organize back stock and ensure products are correctly stored. Confirming all inventory has the pertinent Metrc tag with it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure inventory areas are clean and compliant with health and safety regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop strategies to optimize inventory control procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update inventory records and reconcile weekly shipments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend weekly meetings with Supply Chain, General Manager (GM), &amp;amp; Inventory Manager for open communication and alignment, ensuring that inventory operations are well-integrated with overall store management and supply chain processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum High School Diploma or G.E.D equivalent required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of previous inventory experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Marijuana knowledge strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be over 21 years of age.&lt;/li&gt;

